{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|Encomia|title', 'text' : 'Encomia for the Dormition of the Theotokos'}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|Encomia100|mode', 'text' : 'Mode pl. 1.'}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|Encomia101|text', 'text' : 'In a tomb, O Pure one, you were truly interred, * as the woman who contained God within your womb * and ineffably gave birth to Him on earth.'}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|Encomia102|text', 'text' : 'Mary, as the Mother of the Giver of life, * how can you now die and dwell in a sepulcher, * since your Son has raised the dead out of decay?'}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|Encomia103|text', 'text' : 'He who set the measures of the earth, God the Word, * deigned to be contained, O Pure one, within your womb. * How do you now fit within a tiny tomb?'}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|Encomia104|text', 'text' : 'She who bore the Master, who is handsome and fair * more than any other man, is appearing wan, * now succumbing as she does to nature’s laws.'}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|Encomia105|text', 'text' : 'Through you stripped was Hades, whereas we have been clothed * with the glory of the Lord, O All-holy one. * So how is it that you bow to nature’s laws?'}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|Encomia106|text', 'text' : 'Sting of death was shattered, holy Lady, through you. * We are rid now of corruption. So how is it * that you die and are accounted with the dead?'}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|Encomia107|text', 'text' : 'You contained, O Mary, uncontainable God; * so we wonder how the field of Gethsemane * hides and covers you the holy shrine of God.'}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|Encomia108|text', 'text' : 'Bride of God, O Mary, who gave birth unto to Christ * as an infant here on earth so that He might save * man from death, you have gone down beneath the earth.'}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|Encomia109|text', 'text' : 'Nature and noetic multitudes are amazed * at the mystery of your inexpressible * and all-glorious entombment, Virgin Maid.'}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|Encomia110|text', 'text' : 'Oh, uncommon wonders! Oh, such things that are new! * She who gave birth to the One who gave breath to me * lies now breathless and is buried as one dead.'}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|Encomia111|text', 'text' : 'By divine decision, the Apostles are brought * unto you, O Virgin, lifted up on the clouds, * to inter your holy body in the grave.'}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|Encomia112|text', 'text' : 'The noetic armies in their multitudes run * with Apostles and the Saints to your funeral, * O immaculate, the Mother of our God.'}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|Encomia113|text', 'text' : 'Powers, Thrones, Dominions, Cherubim, Seraphim, * Principalities and Virtues together sing * and with rev’rence honor your falling asleep.'}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|Encomia114|text', 'text' : 'You have died succumbing to the law of all flesh, * even you who had defied nature’s ordinance, * pure and Virgin Mother, in your giving birth.'}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|Encomia115|text', 'text' : 'The noetic orders, O immaculate Maid, * seeing you supine and dead, were beside themselves; * in astonishment they hid beneath their wings.'}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|Encomia116|text', 'text' : 'O pure Maid, the Angels singing heavenly hymns * praised in song your three-day funeral and burial, * and they magnified the glory that is yours.'}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|Encomia117|text', 'text' : 'Like another heaven did the all-holy town * of Gethsemane become when it had received * your all-spotless body, O all-blessed one.'}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|Encomia118|text', 'text' : 'Wherever the body of the Mother of God * has its dwelling, there the troops of the heavenly * and angelic powers rev’rently abide.'}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|Encomia119|text', 'text' : 'Wider than the heavens did the Son of our God * make your body, O immaculate Bride of God, * and your womb He truly made a divine throne.'}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|Encomia120|text', 'text' : 'Seeing dead and speechless you the Mother of Life, * the Disciples of the Word were beside themselves, * O pure Maiden, with astonishment and awe.'}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|Encomia121|text', 'text' : 'While a grave now covers your pure body, O Maid, * yet your Son has your divine soul in His embrace; * and He carries it resplendently aloft.'}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|Encomia122|text', 'text' : 'Though confined, O Mary, in the tiniest tomb, * yet by all creation you are acknowledged as * Queen of heaven and the earth, O Virgin pure.'}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|Encomia123|text', 'text' : 'Even though we see you as one dead in a tomb, * yet we know that you are clearly the Mother of * Jesus God the Word, and Bride of the Most High.'}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|Encomia124|text', 'text' : 'Even though we see you as a mortal entombed, * yet we know you and proclaim you the flower of  * incorruption and the Mother of our God.'}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|Encomia125|text', 'text' : 'We the faithful know you to be truly the key * to Kingdom of our God, Ever-virgin Maid, * even though the tomb conceals you as one dead.'}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|Encomia126|text', 'text' : 'You became the portal of salvation for us, * and the author of our spiritual renaissance, * even if you now submit to natural death.'}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|Encomia127|text', 'text' : 'Now the tomb contains you as the jar, which of old * once contained heavenly manna, O Virgin pure, * and all-holy Lady, and the cause of Life.'}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|Encomia128|text', 'text' : 'Now the rod that blossomed the sweet bud, namely Christ, * has been buried in the earth in a sepulcher, * so that she might bear for us salvation's fruit.'}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|Encomia129|text', 'text' : 'Lady, as a symbol of the comfort you give * to those weeping, by the Valley of Weeping has * your immaculate pure body been interred.'}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|Encomia130|text', 'text' : 'O all-blameless Lady, your own body was laid * there where all the dead and the living will then be judged, * as a means to importune the Judge of all.'}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|Encomia131|text', 'text' : 'Among mortals truly you alone have shone forth * as a type of Resurrection, all-lauded one; * you alone appease the Lord for those who sin.'}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|Encomia132|text', 'text' : 'You became the throne of the Most High, O pure Maid; * now from earth you are transported to heaven's realm, * being translated to everlasting life.'}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|Encomia133|text', 'text' : 'When the congregation of Apostles arrived * at your funeral they cried out and beat their breasts, * and lamenting they did mourn their loss of you.'}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|Encomia134|text', 'text' : 'Having by your childbirth killed the enemy death, * to immortal dwellings you are transported now, * since you bowed to mortal nature's laws and died.'}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|Encomia135|text', 'text' : 'The angelic choirs in the heavens rejoiced * in receiving you, O pure one, as you were led * up from the earth into the heavenly abodes.'}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|Encomia136|text', 'text' : 'As of old you gave birth, passing reason and speech, * even so now you, O pure one, were translated * paradoxic'ly to heaven from the earth.'}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|Encomia137|text', 'text' : 'Virgin, earth and heaven have been filled with delight; * for through you, who were most wondrously taken up * to the heights, they are united after all.'}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|Encomia138|text', 'text' : 'Now you stand beside God in the heights, being dressed * in the variegated graces, as David said, * as the Queen and as the Mother of our God.'}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|Encomia139|text', 'text' : 'You were paid a visit three days prior to death * from an Angel of the Lord, O all-blameless one; * he informed you of your transfer to the heights.'}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|Encomia140|text', 'text' : 'The Archangel who was sent from heaven to you * brings a palm branch unto you, O all-holy one, * as a symbol of your rising to the heights.'}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|Encomia141|text', 'text' : 'You were filled, O Pure one, with such infinite joy * on receiving from the Archangel Gabriel * the announcement of your transfer to the heights.'}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|Encomia142|text', 'text' : 'The trees of the mountain bow their branches to you, * O Immaculate, and thus do they honor you * as their Mistress, and they show you their respect.'}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|Encomia143|text', 'text' : 'Holy Maid, from heaven unto Zion for you * did the armies of the bodiless powers come * with all rev'rance, with their Master and your Son.'}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|Encomia144|text', 'text' : 'The fearsome Archangel amputated the hands * of the man who so audaciously dared to touch * you, O Lady, God's divine and living Ark.'}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|Encomia145|text', 'text' : 'Wailing lamentations, shedding tears over you, * all your women friends did mourn at your burial. * Your departure was unbearable for them.'}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|Encomia146|text', 'text' : 'As they did at that time, likewise fervently now * we implore you, O our Lady, abandon not * us your servants to be orphans as you part.'}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|Encomia147|text', 'text' : 'From the heavens beckon unto us here on earth * as we honor your Dormition, O Lady pure, * and send down infinite mercy from your Son.'}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|Encomia148|text', 'text' : 'Fountain of the graces, Spring of miracle cures, * we entreat you who possess mercy infinite, * never cease to show your tender love for us.'}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|Encomia149|text', 'text' : 'All the Prophets' sayings are fulfilled now in you, * O all-holy Virgin, Lady immaculate, * in your passing into never-ending life.'}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|Encomia150|text', 'text' : 'Even as your forebear Prophet David once said * in his Book of Psalms, O Lady immaculate, * you now stand beside the throne of God as Queen.'}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|Encomia151|text', 'text' : 'You, the tabernacle of the Logos of God * and His bridal room, indeed had to bodily * rise to mansions in the heavens there to dwell. '}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|Encomia152|text', 'text' : 'Thomas was not present, by divine plan indeed, * at your burial, so that we might also know * your Assumption, O Immaculate and Pure.'}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|Encomia153|text', 'text' : 'Piously he also wished to pay his respects * to your holy body, wholly immaculate, * but instead he found your grave empty indeed.'}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|Encomia154|text', 'text' : 'Come, O you believers, let us piously run * all together to our Mistress's funeral, * as she rises into heaven from the earth.'}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|Encomia155|text', 'text' : 'With the God-inspired men who quoted the Psalms, * let us reverently also sing funeral hymns * at the burial of her who is all pure.'}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|Encomia156|text', 'text' : 'You, O holy Maiden, as the table that held * expiation in abundance, are transferred now * to divine and holy dwellings of delight.'}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|Encomia157|text', 'text' : 'Now the golden lamp-stand, that before had received * the immaculate divine Light, is taken up * to the inner tabernacle of the Lord.'}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|Encomia158|text', 'text' : 'Now the holy ladder, which of old Jacob saw * in a dream, and by which came down the Most High God, * is exalted into heaven from the earth.'}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|Encomia159|text', 'text' : 'Now the bridge that carried those who died in the past, * due to Adam's disobedience, out of death * to immortal Life, is taken up on high.'}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|Encomia160|text', 'text' : 'We on earth join chorus with the heavenly minds, * and the Angels now consort with humanity, * as, O Virgin, you are taken up to God.'}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|Encomia161|text', 'text' : 'As the holy lantern of ineffable Light, * O pure Maiden, never cease from enlightening * from the heavens us your servants here on earth.'}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|Encomia162|text', 'text' : 'As a light and swift cloud, you have been lifted up * through the air to God, O Pure one; do ever rain * drops of your all-holy graces upon us.'}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|Encomia163|text', 'text' : 'In the calmest moorings of ineffable joy * are you moored now, Bride of God; therefore send your aid * to your servants who are storm-tossed on the earth.'}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|Encomia164|text', 'text' : 'In the Most High's dwellings, you, O pure Maiden, dwell; * guard and shelter from all trials this most divine * dwelling wherein God is magnified on earth.'}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|Encomia165|text', 'text' : 'Reinforce the scepters of the Orthodox Kings * and the horn of strength of your pious laity, * for you are the Lady of creation all.'}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|Encomia166|text', 'text' : 'As the navigators look into heaven's vault  * for the North Star, which is fixed, so do all of us * gaze at you, O Maiden pure, for guiding light.'}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|Encomia167|text', 'text' : 'Pride and joy, O Lady, of devout priests are you, * and the bastion of the Church unassailable, * and the helper of ascetic monks and nuns.'}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|Encomia168|text', 'text' : 'We ever proclaim you to be Mother of God * and an all-pure Virgin, for we are Orthodox, * and, all-holy one, we glorify your might.'}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|Encomia169|text', 'text' : 'Now your tomb is gushing streams of graces divine, * and it also pours out healings and cures to all, * even though your body is no longer there.'}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|Encomia170|text', 'text' : 'We believers surely place our good hopes in you, * our unyielding intercessor before the Lord, * and a shelter unassailable and strong.'}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|Encomia171|text', 'text' : 'Pure one, make us worthy to be participants *  in the kingdom of your Son, who is Christ our God. * Intercede with Him unceasingly for this.'}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|Encomia172|text', 'text' : 'For although we daily without thinking transgress * His commandments, and are thus disobedient, * even so never have we renounced His name.'}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|Encomia173|text', 'text' : 'Since you are the mother of the One who is good * and the lover of mankind, hence do good to us * as a good and loving mother that you are.'}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|EncomiaTr|text', 'text' : 'Logos, we extol You as the God over all * with the Father and Your all-holy Spirit too, * and we piously give glory unto You.'}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|EncomiaT|text', 'text' : 'We beatify you, O pure Mother of God, * and we glorify your falling asleep today * and your rising into heaven from the earth.'}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|Encomia1F|text', 'text' : 'In a tomb, O Pure one, you were truly interred, * as the woman who contained God within your womb * and ineffably gave birth to Him on earth.'}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|Encomia200|mode', 'text' : 'Mode pl. 1.'}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|Encomia201|text', 'text' : 'Right it is indeed * that we magnify you who received God; * for you are the animate treasury * of the virtues and of every grace of God.'}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|Encomia202|text', 'text' : 'She who has contained * Him who holds the universe together * and is thus perceived as the house of God * is translated now to heaven, there to dwell.'}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|Encomia203|text', 'text' : 'You depart from us, * O all-venerable Virgin Mother; * even so your blessing and grace divine * have remained on us who piously believe.'}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|Encomia204|text', 'text' : 'Truly has your tomb, * virgin Maid, become for you a stairway * by which you ascended from earth below * to the joy and exultation that cease not.'}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|Encomia205|text', 'text' : 'Miracle indeed! * How, though husbandless, you nurse an infant, * how you have become now a lifeless corpse * yet without corruption, Mother of our God!'}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|Encomia206|text', 'text' : 'Mary, you indeed * raised a victory on mortal nature, * giving birth without seed to Christ; but now * giving in to mortal nature's law you die.'}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|Encomia207|text', 'text' : 'Stairway up to God * is your sepulcher, all-holy Virgin, * leading to the heights those who sing your praise * and who honor your Dormition on this day.'}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|Encomia208|text', 'text' : 'By your childbirth * all the earth, O Pure one, was illumined; * likewise now the atmosphere is sanctified, * O pure Maiden, by your heavenward ascent.'}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|Encomia209|text', 'text' : 'As we offer up * funeral hymns and songs to you, O Maiden, * as if fragrant spices for burial, * we entreat for expiation of sins.'}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|Encomia210|text', 'text' : 'O Immaculate, * this august house, in which lies your casket, * has become for us a reliable * sacred clinic for the body and the soul.'}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|Encomia211|text', 'text' : 'Here, wherein the hosts * of Apostles and the holy Angels * stood around your casket and sang to you, * holy Virgin, do we also stand today.'}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|Encomia212|text', 'text' : 'Now we bring to mind * the sublime and splendid ceremony, * which at your Dormition the company * of Apostles with the Angels then performed.'}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|Encomia213|text', 'text' : 'We, like they did then, * stand in wonderment of your Dormition, * and with fear and joy we are present now, * O Immaculate, at your most sacred tomb.'}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|Encomia214|text', 'text' : 'Fertile like the earth * is Gethsemane, that honored city, * for all people wishing to reap from it * their salvation, Virgin Mother, for all time.'}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|Encomia215|text', 'text' : 'Your tomb here below * and your Son’s on high, O holy Virgin, * elevate the minds of believers all, * and they raise them up to heaven from the earth.'}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|Encomia216|text', 'text' : 'Like a pedestal, * does the Mount of Olives hold your tomb now. * Pure one, from above it was dignified * with the footprints of your Son as with a crown.'}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|Encomia217|text', 'text' : 'Virgin, it is clear * that without you as our mediátrix * we will be unable to walk aright * in the supernatural footsteps of your Son.'}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|Encomia218|text', 'text' : 'All-pure Maid, you are * the new tablet on which the divine Word * has been written. Pray that we be enrolled * in the book of Life, as we sing hymns to you.'}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|Encomia219|text', 'text' : 'Neither orators * nor the Angels have it in their power, * Virgin Mother, worthily to extol * you, the most respected Mother of our God.'}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|Encomia220|text', 'text' : 'He who by a nod * fixed the circle of the earth in the beginning, * made you into heaven when as a babe * He contained himself within your virgin womb.'}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|Encomia221|text', 'text' : 'From your womb your Son * willingly assumed the total Adam, * wishing to eradicate from our race * disobedience that in us was innate.'}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|Encomia222|text', 'text' : 'Shadow of the Law * has been terminated, Virgin Mother, * since you bore the Giver of that same Law, * who illumines us who piously believe.'}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|Encomia223|text', 'text' : 'Virgin pure, for you * in a most extraordinary manner * have the laws of nature been modified, * for your childbirth of God Emmanuel.'}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|Encomia224|text', 'text' : 'Only you appear * unto us as a life-bearing grapevine, * for you bore the ripe Bunch of grapes, your Son, * who makes glad the hearts of us who worship Him.'}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|Encomia225|text', 'text' : 'Moses saw of old * you, O Mary, as the bush that burned not * on Mt. Sinai, for you held in your womb * the divine fire and you also were not burned.'}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|Encomia226|text', 'text' : 'Daniel once saw you * as a mountain that had not been quarried * and from which uncut Christ, the Rock of life, * has been cut without the hand of man, O Maid.'}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|Encomia227|text', 'text' : 'You, O Bride of God, * have appeared as the noetic portal * of the divine orient that appeared * from on high to us the faithful here on earth.'}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|Encomia228|text', 'text' : 'Virgin, you gave birth * to the Light from Light for those in darkness * and the shadow, shining on all the earth; * and for those in error you became the Guide.'}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|Encomia229|text', 'text' : 'You have stayed the force * of corruption and of death, O Virgin, * in that without seed you gave birth to God, * the immortal Master and Giver of Life.'}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|Encomia230|text', 'text' : 'O most glorious * and pure Virgin, you preserved your body * and your soul unblemished before the Lord; * hence your beauty was indeed beloved of Christ.'}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|Encomia231|text', 'text' : 'You, O Maiden, are * a bright pillar that lights up the darkness * caused by sinful passions; you are a cloud * holding dew that brings refreshment in the heat.'}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|Encomia232|text', 'text' : 'Pure one, we know you * as a veritable thriving grapevine * bearing an abundance of tender love * and of grace for all who run to you in faith.'}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|Encomia233|text', 'text' : 'As a field indeed * that was never tilled, all-holy Virgin, * truly you have brought forth the Word of God * as the head of grain who nourishes our souls.'}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|Encomia234|text', 'text' : 'Virgin, you are called * by the faithful all, Luminous Morning, * bringing Christ the true Sun of Righteousness,  * who dispels the gloom of ignorance from us.'}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|Encomia235|text', 'text' : 'Mary, O rejoice! * Through you joy into the world has shone forth, * and the curse against us has been removed, * in that you have borne the Savior here on earth.'}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|Encomia236|text', 'text' : 'Wonder most renowned * among Angels are you truly, Virgin, * and you are the wound most greatly bemourned * by the demons, O pure Mother of our God.'}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|Encomia237|text', 'text' : 'Truly you became * like a fertile tree with fruit most luscious, * by which the believers are all sustained * as they pluck and eat its heavenly fruit.'}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|Encomia238|text', 'text' : 'Height, to which the thoughts * of humanity are hardly able * to ascend, are you, Maiden, and the depth, * which for Angels' eyes is hard to apprehend.'}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|Encomia239|text', 'text' : 'Virgin, only you * are the one God has specially chosen; * for that very reason for you alone * God has done great things, as you yourself once said.'}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|Encomia240|text', 'text' : 'You are beautiful, * and there is no spot on you, O Virgin. * This is what the Bridegroom, who fell in love * with your majesty and comeliness, cries out.'}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|Encomia241|text', 'text' : 'Virgin, there have been * many daughters who for God have acted * valiantly in times passed; but truly you * have surpassed them all and stand above them all.'}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|Encomia242|text', 'text' : 'Therefore, Lady pure, * we sing anthems to extol you glory, * melodies, the fruit of unworthy lips, * and we magnify the Lord, your only Son.'}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|Encomia243|text', 'text' : 'You had in your womb, * O Immaculate, the divine Wisdom * that pours out the streams of immortal Life; * therefore gush forth unto us life-giving streams.'}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|Encomia244|text', 'text' : 'O Immaculate, * with your Son we now participate in * life eternal and incorruptible; * hence we sing to you, O holy one, Rejoice!'}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|Encomia245|text', 'text' : 'Therefore we entreat, * as we bend to you the knees of our hearts, * Lady, do yourself likewise lend an ear * to the voices of your servants when we pray.'}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|Encomia246|text', 'text' : 'Even as through you, * O pure Maiden, the deceased are quickened, * likewise also quicken us who are dead * for committing many voluntary sins.'}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|Encomia247|text', 'text' : 'We commit our will * and volition and our expectation * and our soul and body and spirit too * and our whole life unto you, O Maiden pure.'}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|Encomia248|text', 'text' : 'Having confidence * in you, Lady, as our only refuge, * may we not fall short of our highest hopes, * rather may we all obtain your mighty aid.'}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|Encomia249|text', 'text' : 'Holy Maiden pure, * unto us send forth a mighty scepter, * for beneath your shelter we all have run, * and we earnestly take refuge in your care.'}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|Encomia250|text', 'text' : 'For, O Maiden pure, * we have no other protectress but you * who gave birth to Him who created us. * We present you as our advocate to Him.'}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|Encomia251|text', 'text' : 'Virgin, make us rich * with ideas of things good and noble, * for having transgressed the divine commands * we have mindlessly impoverished our souls.'}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|Encomia252|text', 'text' : 'Give light to the eyes * of our intellect, O Virgin Mary; * by your shining prayers guide us in the ways * of repentance, O all-holy Maiden pure.'}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|Encomia253|text', 'text' : 'Virgin Queen of all, * we your servants pray you make the Master * merciful to us, by your fervent prayers, * when He comes to judge all mortals on that Day.'}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|Encomia254|text', 'text' : 'Maiden, guide us straight * to the peaceful harbor of salvation; * we are tossed about on the sea of life * by the stormy winds of soul-destroying sins.'}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|Encomia255|text', 'text' : 'Water with the rain * of your mercies, Virgin Theotokos, * furrows of our souls, which are overrun * by the sinful passions as with thorny weeds.'}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|Encomia256|text', 'text' : 'Open up the door * of your mercy, O all-holy Maiden, * unto us who now call upon your name; * for you are the timely refuge for mankind.'}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|Encomia257|text', 'text' : 'Maid, instead of myrrh * do accept this period of fasting * that we keep to honor your Burial; * and the death of sinful passions give to us.'}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|Encomia258|text', 'text' : 'As your servants stand * by your sepulcher, all-holy Virgin, * graciously accept the melodious * odes they offer unto you as fragrant oils.'}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|Encomia259|text', 'text' : 'Pure one, we all know, * even if we offer odes in number * equal to the sands unto you, we do * nothing worthy of the gifts you give to us.'}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|Encomia260|text', 'text' : 'Every hymn and ode * is incapable of duly praising * your uncounted graces and all the gifts * we abundantly enjoy because of you.'}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|Encomia2Tr|text', 'text' : 'To the Father, Son * and the holy Spirit we all send up * glory, honor worship most piously, * to the Trinity, all-holy and divine.'}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|Encomia2T|text', 'text' : 'O believers all, * as the servants of the Theotokos, * let us sing her hymns that are Orthodox * and acceptable, extolling her today.'}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|Encomia2F|text', 'text' : 'Right it is indeed * that we magnify you who received God; * for you are the animate treasury * of the virtues and of every grace of God.'}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|Encomia300|mode', 'text' : 'Mode 3.'}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|Encomia301|text', 'text' : 'All generations offer, * O Virgin, hymns in honor * and praise of your entombment.'}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|Encomia302|text', 'text' : 'To death you have submitted, * O Virgin, who gave birth to * Him who dealt death to Hades.'}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|Encomia303|text', 'text' : 'In dying you went over * to the undying dwellings, * putting to death the foe death.'}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|Encomia304|text', 'text' : 'The hearts of all the pious * leap in exultation, * O Lady, at your funeral.'}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|Encomia305|text', 'text' : 'Earth is celebrating * while heaven dances, Lady, * as you are now uplifted.'}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|Encomia306|text', 'text' : 'You hasten to ascend now * into the heights, O Virgin, * being above the earthly.'}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|Encomia307|text', 'text' : 'O Virgin, you were transferred * to heaven, so that you might * behold your Son's great beauty.'}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|Encomia308|text', 'text' : 'You vivified the reaches * of the world, O Virgin, * by your divine Dormition.'}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|Encomia309|text', 'text' : 'Your sepulcher, O Virgin, * delivers us from passions, * and thus proclaims your glory.'}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|Encomia310|text', 'text' : 'Your sepulcher, O Virgin, * proclaims your true entombment * and also your translation.'}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|Encomia311|text', 'text' : 'We think that we are looking * at you, O Theotokos, * when we gaze at your body.'}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|Encomia312|text', 'text' : 'Standing in your temple, * we think that we are standing * in heaven, holy Virgin.'}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|Encomia313|text', 'text' : 'Pray to the Creator, * with the saints together, * O Virgin, and your parents.'}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|Encomia314|text', 'text' : 'Pray that He may count us * the Orthodox believers * worthy of joy forever.'}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|Encomia315|text', 'text' : 'Every nation's people, * O Virgin, call you Lady, * as they now venerate you.'}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|Encomia316|text', 'text' : 'And truly now, O Virgin, * every generation * forever calls you blessed.'}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|Encomia317|text', 'text' : 'Only those who killed Christ * in unbelief deny you * to be the Theotokos.'}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|Encomia318|text', 'text' : 'The other tongues and nations * surround your tomb, O Lady, * and faithfully extol you.'}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|Encomia319|text', 'text' : 'All of us entreat you * to grant us your protection, * O Virgin, and assistance.'}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|Encomia320|text', 'text' : 'No one who seeks refuge * in you, O Virgin Maiden, * departs from you embarrassed.'}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|Encomia321|text', 'text' : 'Imitating your Son * you grant requests, O Lady, * alike to saints and sinners.'}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|Encomia322|text', 'text' : 'For you want all people * to be saved, O Lady, * and to share your glory.'}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|Encomia323|text', 'text' : 'Maiden, we all know you * as one who loves all people, * for you are God's own Mother.'}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|Encomia324|text', 'text' : 'Who can truly tell of * your divine virtues, * O only Virgin Mother?'}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|Encomia325|text', 'text' : 'And who can list the blessings * that you give, O Lady, * so richly to all people?'}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|Encomia326|text', 'text' : 'Unto those who trust you, * both deceased and living, * You provide assistance.'}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|Encomia327|text', 'text' : 'You do whatever you wish, * for you can do all things * as Mother of the Most High.'}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|Encomia328|text', 'text' : 'Therefore, Maiden, guard us, * both deceased and living * who ever sing your praises.'}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|Encomia329|text', 'text' : 'Deliver us, O Virgin, * from the everlasting * fire of Gehenna.'}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|Encomia330|text', 'text' : 'You are the lone protectress * of poor and homeless people * and of orphans and widows.'}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|Encomia331|text', 'text' : 'And you are the sweetness * of Angels, Virgin Mary, * the joy of those in sorrow.'}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|Encomia332|text', 'text' : 'We all proclaim that you are * the shelter for us Christians, * indeed even our Mother.'}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|Encomia333|text', 'text' : 'By your intercessions, * raise us who have fallen * into the depths of evil.'}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|Encomia334|text', 'text' : 'Help us who revere you, * O virgin Maid, to follow * the footsteps of the Master.'}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|Encomia335|text', 'text' : 'While we are gripped in evils, * do not despise us, Virgin, * lest we utterly perish.'}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|Encomia336|text', 'text' : 'Knowingly and also * unconsciously we all sin, * offending you and your Son.'}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|Encomia337|text', 'text' : 'Nonetheless, we pray now * that you will not reject us, * O Virgin, from your presence.'}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|Encomia338|text', 'text' : 'Entreat your Son, O Lady, * that He will show compassion * on us when He will judge us.'}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|Encomia339|text', 'text' : 'For we know the power * of your intercession * upon your Son, O Maiden.'}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|Encomia340|text', 'text' : 'Many times you only * were able to appease Him * when we provoked His anger.'}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|Encomia341|text', 'text' : 'He honors you, His Mother, * and bends to your entreaties, * for you are due all glory.'}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|Encomia342|text', 'text' : 'As is right we also * with longing venerate you, * and sing hymns in your honor.'}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|Encomia343|text', 'text' : 'Through you, all-holy Maiden, * God the Logos truly * has recreated our race.'}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|Encomia344|text', 'text' : 'And through you He saves us, * who have taken refuge * in you, all-lauded Mary.'}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|Encomia345|text', 'text' : 'For you are God's chosen * instrument, O Virgin, * of humankind's salvation.'}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|Encomia346|text', 'text' : 'Therefore as you know best * do good to all your servants, * O Virgin Theotokos.'}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|Encomia347|text', 'text' : 'When burying your body, * with fragrant oils they sprinkled * your tomb, O holy Virgin.'}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|Encomia348|text', 'text' : 'Those present at your funeral * with fragrant oils and flowers * sprinkled your tomb, O Virgin.'}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|Encomia349|text', 'text' : 'Those present at your funeral * with fragrant oils sprinkled * your tomb, O Theotokos.'}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|Encomia3Tr|text', 'text' : 'Father, Son and Spirit, * the Trinity, we pray You, * save us who adore You.'}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|Encomia3T|text', 'text' : 'O all-holy Mother, * guard and shelter all those * who trust in you, O Lady.'}
{'id_' : 'other|dormitionencomia_en_US_dedes|other|Encomia3F|text', 'text' : 'All generations offer, * O Virgin, hymns in honor * and praise of your entombment.'}
